### Function definitions
def read_csv(filename):
    '''Read in .csv file and remove masked rows'''
    # Begin by reading in the .csv file
    cluster = ascii.read(filename, format='csv')
    # Remove rows that have masked G_BP or G_RP photometry values (all rows have G photometry values)
    cluster = cluster[(~cluster['phot_bp_mean_mag'].mask) & (~cluster['phot_rp_mean_mag'].mask)]
    return cluster

def convert_gaia_to_jc(G, G_BP, G_RP):
    '''Convert Gaia photometry to V and I passbands'''
    # Begin by converting G_BP - G_RP to V - I
    G_BP_minus_G_RP = G_BP - G_RP
    c, c1, c2 = -0.04212, 1.286, -0.09494
    c0 = c - G_BP_minus_G_RP
    V_minus_I = (-c1 + np.sqrt((c1**2) - (4*c2*c0)))/(2*c2)
    # Then convert V - I to G - V and solve for V
    d0, d1, d2, d3 = -0.01746, 0.008092, -0.2810, 0.03655
    G_minus_V = d0 + d1*V_minus_I + d2*(V_minus_I**2) + d3*(V_minus_I**3)
    V = -G_minus_V + G
    return V, V_minus_I

def plot_cmd(V_minus_I, V, cluster, fn, color, cmd_type):
    '''Plot a color magnitude diagram'''
    plt.figure(dpi = display_dpi)
    plt.plot(V_minus_I, V, 'o'+color, ms = 0.5)
    plt.gca().invert_yaxis()
    plt.xlabel(r"V $-$ I")
    plt.ylabel("V")
    plt.title(cluster+" "+cmd_type+" Color Magnitude Diagram")
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.savefig("figures/"+fn+"_cmd.png", dpi = 300, facecolor='w', edgecolor='w')
    plt.show()
    
def plot_pmd(pmra, pmdec, cluster, fn, color, pmd_type, xlims = None, ylims = None):
    '''Plot a proper motion diagram'''
    plt.figure(dpi = display_dpi)
    plt.plot(pmra, pmdec, 'o'+color, ms = 0.5)
    plt.xlabel(r"Right ascension proper motion ($\mu_{\mathrm{RA}} \cos(\delta),\ \mathrm{mas\ yr^{-1}}$)")
    plt.ylabel(r"Declination proper motion ($\mu_{\mathrm{dec}},\ \mathrm{mas\ yr^{-1}}$)")
    if xlims is not None and ylims is not None:
        plt.xlim(xlims[0], xlims[1])
        plt.ylim(ylims[0], ylims[1])
    plt.title(cluster+" "+pmd_type+" Proper Motion Diagram")
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.savefig("figures/"+fn+"_pmd.png", dpi = 300, facecolor='w', edgecolor='w')
    plt.show()
    
def gaussian(x, a, mu, sigma):
    return a*np.exp(-.5*(x-mu)**2/(sigma**2))

def double_gaussian(x, a1, mu1, sigma1, a2, mu2, sigma2):
    return a1*np.exp(-.5*(x-mu1)**2/(sigma1**2)) + a2*np.exp(-.5*(x-mu2)**2/(sigma2**2))

def fit_proper_motions(arr, fit_type, cluster, color, data_type, guesses = None):
    '''Fit one or two Gaussian functions to binned data and return fit parameters'''
    binsize = 0.5
    # Bin data and fit Gaussian function(s) to the bins
    counts, bins = np.histogram(arr.ravel(), bins=np.arange(np.min(arr), np.max(arr), binsize))
    if fit_type == 'single':
        popt, pcov = curve_fit(gaussian, xdata=bins[:-1], ydata=counts, p0=guesses) # len 3
        fit = gaussian(bins[:-1], *popt)
    elif fit_type == 'double':
        popt, pcov = curve_fit(double_gaussian, xdata=bins[:-1], ydata=counts, p0=guesses) # len 6
        fit = double_gaussian(bins[:-1], *popt)
    # Plot histogram and fit
    plt.figure(dpi = display_dpi)
    plt.step(bins[:-1]+(binsize/2.0), counts, color=color, label="binned data")
    plt.plot(bins[:-1], fit, 'k', label="Gaussian fit(s)")
    if data_type == 'RA':
        plt.xlabel(r"Right ascension proper motion ($\mu_{\mathrm{RA}} \cos(\delta),\ \mathrm{mas\ yr^{-1}}$)")
        plt.title(cluster+r" $\mu_{\mathrm{RA}} \cos(\delta)$ Proper Motion Histogram")
    elif data_type == 'dec':
        plt.xlabel(r"Declination proper motion ($\mu_{\mathrm{dec}},\ \mathrm{mas\ yr^{-1}}$)")
        plt.title(cluster+r" $\mu_{\mathrm{dec}}$ Proper Motion Histogram")
    plt.ylabel("Counts per bin")
    plt.legend(loc="best")
#     plt.savefig("figures/"+cluster+"_"+data_type+"_hist.png", dpi = 300, facecolor='w', edgecolor='w')
    plt.show()
    return popt

def fit_parallax(arr, cluster, fn, color, guesses = None):
    '''Fit a Gaussian function to binned data and return fit parameters'''
    binsize = 0.05
    # Bin data and fit Gaussian function(s) to the bins
    counts, bins = np.histogram(arr.ravel(), bins=np.arange(np.min(arr), np.max(arr), binsize))
    popt, pcov = curve_fit(gaussian, xdata=bins[:-1], ydata=counts, p0=guesses) # len 3
    fit = gaussian(bins[:-1], *popt)
    # Plot binned histogram and fit
    plt.figure(dpi = display_dpi)
    plt.step(bins[:-1]+(binsize/2.0), counts, color=color, label="binned data")
    plt.plot(bins[:-1], fit, 'k', label="Gaussian fit")
    plt.xlabel("Parallax (mas)")
    plt.ylabel("Counts per bin")
    plt.title(cluster+" Parallax Binned Histogram")
    plt.legend(loc="best")
    plt.savefig("figures/"+fn+"_parallax_binned_hist.png", dpi = 300, facecolor='w', edgecolor='w')
    plt.show()
    # Plot generalized histogram
    plt.figure(dpi = display_dpi)
    plt.plot(bins[:-1]+(binsize/2.0), counts, color)
    plt.xlabel("Parallax (mas)")
    plt.ylabel("Counts per bin")
    plt.title(cluster+" Parallax Generalized Histogram")
    plt.savefig("figures/"+fn+"_parallax_general_hist.png", dpi = 300, facecolor='w', edgecolor='w')
    return popt

def plot_ind_cmd(V_minus_I_0, M_V, cluster, fn, color):
    '''Plot a color magnitude diagram with absolute magnitudes'''
    plt.figure(dpi = display_dpi)
    plt.plot(V_minus_I_0, M_V, 'o'+color, ms = 0.5)
    plt.gca().invert_yaxis()
    plt.xlabel(r"(V $-$ I$)_0$")
    plt.ylabel(r"$M$\textsubscript{V}")
    plt.title(cluster+" Ind.-corr. Color Magnitude Diagram")
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.savefig("figures/"+fn+"_ind_corr_cmd.png", dpi = 300, facecolor='w', edgecolor='w')
    plt.show()
    
def plot_cluster_cmd(V_minus_I_0, M_V, cluster, fn, color):
    '''Plot a color magnitude diagram with absolute magnitudes'''
    plt.figure(dpi = display_dpi)
    plt.plot(V_minus_I_0, M_V, 'o'+color, ms = 0.5)
    plt.gca().invert_yaxis()
    plt.xlabel(r"(V $-$ I$)_0$")
    plt.ylabel(r"$M$\textsubscript{V}")
    plt.title(cluster+" Cluster-corrected Color Magnitude Diagram")
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.savefig("figures/"+fn+"_cluster_corr_cmd.png", dpi = 300, facecolor='w', edgecolor='w')
    plt.show()
    
def luminosity_function(arr, cluster, fn, color):
    binsize = 0.1
    # Bin data 
    counts, bins = np.histogram(arr.ravel(), bins=np.arange(np.nanmin(arr), np.nanmax(arr), binsize))
    plt.figure(dpi = display_dpi)
    plt.plot(bins[:-1]+(binsize/2.0), counts/max(counts), color)
    plt.xlim(-5,15)
    plt.gca().invert_xaxis()
    plt.xlabel(r"$M$\textsubscript{V}")
    plt.ylabel("Fractional counts per bin")
    plt.title(cluster+" Norm. Generalized Luminosity Function")
    plt.savefig("figures/"+fn+"_lum.png", dpi = 300, facecolor='w', edgecolor='w')
    plt.show()
    
def c_luminosity_function(arr, cluster, fn, color):
    binsize = 0.1
    # Bin data 
    counts, bins = np.histogram(arr.ravel(), bins=np.arange(np.nanmin(arr), np.nanmax(arr), binsize))
    # Loop through counts and keep track of cumulative count
    running_count = 0.
    cumulative_counts = []
    for i in range(len(counts)):
        running_count += counts[len(counts)-1-i] # Reverse direction because of how magnitude is defined
        cumulative_counts.append(running_count)
    plt.figure(dpi = display_dpi)
    plt.plot(bins[:-1]+(binsize/2.0), cumulative_counts[::-1]/max(cumulative_counts), color) # Reverse again
    plt.xlim(-5,15)
    plt.gca().invert_xaxis() # Reverse a third time
    plt.xlabel(r"$M$\textsubscript{V}")
    plt.ylabel("Fractional cumulative counts per bin")
    plt.title(cluster+" Norm. Cumulative Luminosity Function")
    plt.savefig("figures/"+fn+"_c_lum.png", dpi = 300, facecolor='w', edgecolor='w')
    plt.show()

### M67

# Front matter
color = 'm'
M67 = read_csv('M67-result.csv')
M67['V'], M67['V_minus_I'] = convert_gaia_to_jc(M67['phot_g_mean_mag'], 
                                                M67['phot_bp_mean_mag'], 
                                                M67['phot_rp_mean_mag'])

# Rough color magnitude diagram
plot_cmd(M67['V_minus_I'], M67['V'], 'M67', 'M67_rough', color, 'Rough')

# Rough proper motion diagram
plot_pmd(M67['pmra'], M67['pmdec'], 'M67', 'M67_rough', color, 'Rough',
         xlims = (-14, -8), ylims = (-5, -1))

# Determining center and width
RA_a, RA_mu, RA_sigma, \
RA_a2, RA_mu2, RA_sigma2 = fit_proper_motions(M67['pmra'], 'double', 'M67', color, 'RA', 
                                              guesses = [600,-15,2,1200,-2,2])
dec_a, dec_mu, dec_sigma = fit_proper_motions(M67['pmdec'], 'single', 'M67', color, 'dec', 
                                              guesses = [400,0,0.1])
print("RA center: ",RA_mu)
print("RA 3sigma width: ", 3*np.abs(RA_sigma))
print("Dec center: ",dec_mu)
print("Dec 3sigma width: ", 3*np.abs(dec_sigma))

# Determine cluster members
RA_ll, RA_ul = RA_mu - 3*np.abs(RA_sigma), RA_mu + 3*np.abs(RA_sigma)
dec_ll, dec_ul = dec_mu - 3*np.abs(dec_sigma), dec_mu + 3*np.abs(dec_sigma)
M67_members = M67[(M67['pmra'] >= RA_ll) & (M67['pmra'] <= RA_ul) & 
                  (M67['pmdec'] >= dec_ll) & (M67['pmdec'] <= dec_ul)]

# Member color magnitude diagram
plot_cmd(M67_members['V_minus_I'], M67_members['V'], 'M67', 'M67_member', color, 'Member')

# Parallax histograms
p_a, p_mu, p_sigma = fit_parallax(M67_members['parallax'], 'M67', 'M67', color, 
                                  guesses = [30, 1.1, 0.1])
print("Parallax: ",p_mu)
p_error = p_sigma/np.sqrt(len(M67_members))
print("Parallax 1sigma error: ",p_error)

# Distance
p_frac_error = p_error/p_mu
dist = ((p_mu*u.mas).to(u.arcsec)).to(u.parsec, equivalencies=u.parallax())
dist_error = dist*p_frac_error
print("Distance: ",dist)
print("Distance error: ",dist_error)

# Distance modulus
dist_mod = 5.*np.log10(dist.value) - 5.
dist_mod_error = 5.*dist_error/(dist*np.log(10.))
print("Distance modulus: ",dist_mod)
print("Distance modulus error: ",dist_mod_error)

# Literature parallax angle to distance modulus
lit_p = 1.1325*u.mas
lit_p_error = 0.0011*u.mas
lit_p_frac_error = lit_p_error/lit_p
lit_dist = (lit_p.to(u.arcsec)).to(u.parsec, equivalencies=u.parallax())
lit_dist_error = lit_dist*lit_p_frac_error
lit_dist_mod = 5.*np.log10(lit_dist.value) - 5.
lit_dist_mod_error = 5.*lit_dist_error/(lit_dist*np.log(10.))
print("Literature distance modulus: ",lit_dist_mod)
print("Literature distance modulus error: ",lit_dist_mod_error)

# Individual distance- and reddening- corrected CMD
A_V = 0.094
d = ((M67_members['parallax']*u.mas).to(u.arcsec)).to(u.parsec, equivalencies=u.parallax())
m = M67_members['V']
M67_members['M_V'] = m + 5 - A_V - 5.*np.log10(d.value)
M67_members['V_minus_I_0'] = M67_members['V_minus_I'] - (A_V/2.5)
plot_ind_cmd(M67_members['V_minus_I_0'], M67_members['M_V'], 'M67', 'M67', color)

# Cluster distance- and reddening- corrected CMD
M67_members['M_V_c'] = m + 5 - A_V - 5.*np.log10(dist.value) # use dist here, which is cluster-averaged
plot_cluster_cmd(M67_members['V_minus_I_0'], M67_members['M_V_c'], 'M67', 'M67', color)

# Luminosity function (normalized generalized histogram)
luminosity_function(M67_members['M_V'], 'M67', 'M67', color)

# Luminosity function (normalized cumulative histogram)
c_luminosity_function(M67_members['M_V'], 'M67', 'M67', color)

### NGC 6791

# Front matter
color = 'g'
NGC6791 = read_csv('NGC6791-result.csv')
NGC6791['V'], NGC6791['V_minus_I'] = convert_gaia_to_jc(NGC6791['phot_g_mean_mag'],
                                                        NGC6791['phot_bp_mean_mag'], 
                                                        NGC6791['phot_rp_mean_mag'])

# Rough color magnitude diagram
plot_cmd(NGC6791['V_minus_I'], NGC6791['V'], 'NGC 6791', 'NGC6791_rough', color, 'Rough')

# Rough proper motion diagram
plot_pmd(NGC6791['pmra'], NGC6791['pmdec'], 'NGC 6791', 'NGC6791_rough', color, 'Rough',
         xlims = (-1.5, 0.5), ylims = (-3.5, -1))

# Determining center and width
RA_a, RA_mu, RA_sigma = fit_proper_motions(NGC6791['pmra'], 'single', 'NGC 6791', color, 'RA', 
                                           guesses = [1400,-15,2])
dec_a, dec_mu, dec_sigma = fit_proper_motions(NGC6791['pmdec'], 'single', 'NGC 6791', color, 'dec', 
                                              guesses = [3000,-5,2])
print("RA center: ",RA_mu)
print("RA 3sigma width: ", 3*np.abs(RA_sigma))
print("Dec center: ",dec_mu)
print("Dec 3sigma width: ", 3*np.abs(dec_sigma))

# Determine cluster members
RA_ll, RA_ul = RA_mu - 3*np.abs(RA_sigma), RA_mu + 3*np.abs(RA_sigma)
dec_ll, dec_ul = dec_mu - 3*np.abs(dec_sigma), dec_mu + 3*np.abs(dec_sigma)
NGC6791_members = NGC6791[(NGC6791['pmra'] >= RA_ll) & (NGC6791['pmra'] <= RA_ul) & 
                          (NGC6791['pmdec'] >= dec_ll) & (NGC6791['pmdec'] <= dec_ul)]

# Member color magnitude diagram
plot_cmd(NGC6791_members['V_minus_I'], NGC6791_members['V'], 'NGC 6791', 'NGC6791_member', color, 'Member')

# Parallax histograms
p_a, p_mu, p_sigma = fit_parallax(NGC6791_members['parallax'], 'NGC 6791', 'NGC6791', color, 
                                  guesses = [500, 0.1, 0.1])
print("Parallax: ",p_mu)
p_error = p_sigma/np.sqrt(len(NGC6791_members))
print("Parallax 1sigma error: ",p_error)

# Distance
p_frac_error = p_error/p_mu
dist = ((p_mu*u.mas).to(u.arcsec)).to(u.parsec, equivalencies=u.parallax())
dist_error = dist*p_frac_error
print("Distance: ",dist)
print("Distance error: ",dist_error)

# Distance modulus
dist_mod = 5.*np.log10(dist.value) - 5.
dist_mod_error = 5.*dist_error/(dist*np.log(10.))
print("Distance modulus: ",dist_mod)
print("Distance modulus error: ",dist_mod_error)

# Literature parallax angle to distance modulus
lit_p = 0.192*u.mas
lit_p_error = 0.084*u.mas
lit_p_frac_error = lit_p_error/lit_p
lit_dist = (lit_p.to(u.arcsec)).to(u.parsec, equivalencies=u.parallax())
lit_dist_error = lit_dist*lit_p_frac_error
lit_dist_mod = 5.*np.log10(lit_dist.value) - 5.
lit_dist_mod_error = 5.*lit_dist_error/(lit_dist*np.log(10.))
print("Literature distance modulus: ",lit_dist_mod)
print("Literature distance modulus error: ",lit_dist_mod_error)

# Individual distance- and reddening- corrected CMD
A_V = 0.425
d = ((NGC6791_members['parallax']*u.mas).to(u.arcsec)).to(u.parsec, equivalencies=u.parallax())
m = NGC6791_members['V']
NGC6791_members['M_V'] = m + 5 - A_V - 5.*np.log10(d.value)
NGC6791_members['V_minus_I_0'] = NGC6791_members['V_minus_I'] - (A_V/2.5)
plot_ind_cmd(NGC6791_members['V_minus_I_0'], NGC6791_members['M_V'], 'NGC 6791', 'NGC6791', color)

# Cluster distance- and reddening- corrected CMD
NGC6791_members['M_V_c'] = m + 5 - A_V - 5.*np.log10(dist.value) # use dist here, which is cluster-averaged
plot_cluster_cmd(NGC6791_members['V_minus_I_0'], NGC6791_members['M_V_c'], 'NGC 6791', 'NGC6791', color)

# Luminosity function (normalized generalized histogram)
luminosity_function(NGC6791_members['M_V'], 'NGC 6791', 'NGC6791', color)

# Luminosity function (normalized cumulative histogram)
c_luminosity_function(NGC6791_members['M_V'], 'NGC 6791', 'NGC6791', color)
